EN: Migrant flows between regions of the World, 2010-2015

The arrows' width represents the number of migrants. The numbers around the circle shows the scale in million of migrants. The total number of people worldwide who left their native countries between 2010 and 2015 is 36.5 million or 0.5% of the world’s population.
Guy J. Abel (Asian Demographic Research Institute, Shanghai University & Vienna Institute of Demography, Austrian Academy of Sciences)
